Summaries for FDFT1 Gene

Entrez Gene Summary for FDFT1 Gene

  • This gene encodes a membrane-associated enzyme located at a branch point in the mevalonate pathway. The encoded protein is the first specific enzyme in cholesterol biosynthesis, catalyzing the dimerization of two molecules of farnesyl diphosphate in a two-step reaction to form squalene. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008]

GeneCards Summary for FDFT1 Gene

FDFT1 (Farnesyl-Diphosphate Farnesyltransferase 1) is a Protein Coding gene. Diseases associated with FDFT1 include congenital disorder of glycosylation, type ij and myasthenic syndrome, congenital, 13, with tubular aggregates. Among its related pathways are Metabolism and cholesterol biosynthesis II (via 24,25-dihydrolanosterol). GO annotations related to this gene include oxidoreductase activity and farnesyl-diphosphate farnesyltransferase activity.

No data available for UniProtKB/Swiss-Prot , Tocris Summary , Gene Wiki entry , PharmGKB "VIP" Summary , fRNAdb sequence ontologies and piRNA Summary for FDFT1 Gene
